# Routing & layouts

## Adding a page

1. Create view in `src/views/<area>/<Page>.tsx` (thin wrapper)
2. Lazy-import in `src/routes/Router.tsx` with `Loadable(lazy(...))`
3. Add route under `FullLayout` or `BlankLayout` children
4. Add sidebar entry in `src/layouts/full/vertical/sidebar/sidebaritems.ts`

```tsx
// Router.tsx pattern
const MyPage = Loadable(lazy(() => import('../views/area/MyPage')));
// ...
{ path: '/my-page', element: <MyPage /> },
```

- **FullLayout**: authenticated pages with sidebar + header
- **BlankLayout**: auth and standalone error pages
- Catch-all `*` routes redirect to `/auth/404`
- Keep route paths lowercase with kebab-case segments
